author: {'id': 1578480355, 'name': 'Brian M. Johnson, Jillian Gurry'}
body:
Thomaston Savings Bank employees donate to local organizations through The Great Give 150 initiative.
BRISTOL — Thomaston Savings Bank employees have donated $33,150 to 109 area organizations as part of the bank’s “Great Give 150” initiative. Some of the recipients include several greater Bristol children, family, veteran and service organizations.
 Thomaston Savings Bank hosted The Great Give 150 initiative to commemorate the Bank’s 150th anniversary and “propel the Bank’s culture of giving.” The Thomaston Savings Bank Foundation allocated $150 to each employee to donate to a charity of their choice within the Bank’s footprint.

author: {'id': 1067873720}
body:
Thomaston Savings Bank promoted three new executives, including a new executive vice president, on Friday.
Rebekah Stokes has been elevated to executive vice president and chief financial officer, her latest move in a career that started at the bank in 2001 as a teller. She joined Thomaston Savings’ finance department in 2008 and was promoted to vice president and senior financial officer in 2016 and to senior vice president chief financial officer in 2019.
 Jen Wabiszczewicz has been named the bank’s new controller and promoted to vice president. Wabiszczewicz joined the bank in 1998 and was most recently assistant vice president and accounting manager in 2023.
 Chad Belanger was named the bank’s new treasurer and was promoted to vice president. Like Wabiszczewicz and Stokes, he also started out at the bank as a teller – in his case in 2006 and 2007 in the bank’s “School-to-Career” program. He rejoined the bank in 2011 and most recently held the position of assistant vice president and treasury analyst.

author: {'id': 1067334722}
body:
THOMASTON — Thomaston Savings Bank employees raised a total of $11,160 for local organizations through their Denim Days over the last six months. The bank's Denim Days allow employees to wear jeans on Fridays throughout the month for a small donation to a preselected local nonprofit which provides vital services to the community. If employees donate a total of $1,000 or more throughout the month, the bank contributes an additional $1,000 to that month's cause.
 “We are so grateful for the funding from Thomaston Savings Bank's Denim Days. These funds will be used toward our personal development classes. Together we are transforming lives!” said Christine Nelson, executive director, Thy Eagle's Nest.
  The recipients include Brian O'Connell Homeless Project, FISH (Friends in Service to Humanity), the Plainville Food Pantry, Thomaston Community Pantry, Thy Eagle's Nest and Brian's Angels Homeless Outreach. The bank will continue this employee campaign through 2024.
  To learn more about Thomaston Savings Bank and the services they offer, visit ThomastonSB.com

title: Thomaston Savings Bank Employees Raise Eleven Thousand for Local Organizations

author: {'id': 976729}
body:
NEW BRITAIN — While many have seen the disappearing of their bank or banks over the past two decades, there is new dance partner in the heart of downtown New Britain.
Connecticut banks, like other states have been bought out, consolidated, merged and so forth. One’s new choice could be that of the Thomaston Savings Bank on the corner of Main and Bank streets. Thomaston will celebrate its 150th anniversary in 2024.
 On a bright, brisk and sunny day, many gathered for the ribbon cutting at 233 Main Street, with the likes of city representatives, patrons, passer-byes and many bank officials from all 16 branches.

author: {'id': 27641555, 'name': 'Blaine Callahan'}
body:
New Britain is getting a new Thomaston Savings Bank branch at 233 Main St., according to a press release.

The bank will have bilingual staff fluent in both Spanish and Polish.

Each branch location has a “specialized team” that includes a commercial lender, business development officer, residential lender and broker to aid clients with their needs and objectives.

“We are delighted to join the New Britain community,” said Stephen Lewis, president and CEO of Thomaston Savings Bank. “This new location will continue to bring high quality customer service, a robust product suite, and a bilingual team ready to help you on your financial journey. We look forward to serving our new neighbors.”

You can find more information on Thomaston Savings Bank here.

author: {'id': 3058627}
body:
Have you ever had your social media account hacked? Got a friend suggestion of yourself? It's an awful feeling, and it happens to everyone, even local banks. I'm a Thomaston Savings Bank customer, and they've just sent out an alert warning their customers to be aware that they've recently had someone attempting to duplicate their official profile on Facebook.

Get our free mobile app

First and foremost, it's 2023, and even if there's a blue check mark on whatever verified social media account there is, I will never provide any kind of personal information online. Be like me. According to the official Thomaston Savings Bank Facebook account, there has reportedly been an attempt to duplicate the official account. The statement from Thomaston Savings bank goes on to state that they will never reach out to their customers via their personal profiles or ask for any kind of sensitive information through comments on photos or posts.

At this moment, Thomaston Savings Bank has asked us customers to not engage with anyone claiming to be Thomaston Savings Bank on our shared posts or photos, and to report those posted comments immediately. If you've had any recent interaction, or any concerns or questions Thomaston Savings bank has requested that you reach out through their official customer service channels, which are: thomastonsavingsbank.com, 860-283-1874, or 855-344-1874.

I'll follow up their official statement by adding that you should see a red flag go up if any local bank likes your photo of the craft beer cooler at The Market CT - Bantam, and instead of asking what IPA that is, they ask for you annual income. Immediately skeptical, that's the way to operate online in 2023.

My Favorite Art Gallery is The Market-Bantam Craft Beer Cooler I have to hand it to you craft beer makers of Connecticut, you use such beautiful artwork on your cans. My wife and I wandered into the awesome craft beer cooler at The Market-Bantam the other night, and spent about 15 minutes appreciating the 38 degree art gallery.

The Many Faces of 545 Main Street in Watertown, Connecticut The first restaurant that I remember being in that beautiful old bank building was Heminway's, then it passed through quite a few hands. Remember some of these great, and not so great identities of 545 Main Street in Watertown over the past 30 years?

 Where it’s available : CT
 How to earn it : This offer is for their consumer mortgage customers only.
 Thomaston Savings Bank offers a $500 bonus for opening a new personal checking account.
 To qualify for the bonus, you need to enroll in eStatements.
 You also need to set up at least $1,000 in direct deposits.
 The $500 bonus is provided by Thomaston Savings Bank.
 The offer is specifically for new customers who meet the requirements.
 The bonus is a reward for choosing Thomaston Savings Bank for your personal checking needs.
 When it expires: Not stated

body:
Maximum bonus amount: $500 Availability: CT Direct deposit required:
Yes, $1,000+
 Additional requirements: eStatements
 Hard/soft pull: Unknown
 ChexSystems: Unknown
 Credit card funding: Unknown
 Monthly fees: None
 Early account termination fee: None
 Household limit: None
 Expiration date: None listed
 The Offer Thomaston Savings Bank is offering a $500 when you open a new Thomaston Savings Bank personal checking account and complete the following requirements:
 enroll in eStatements set up $1,000 in direct deposits
 The Fine Print Offer is only available to new Thomaston Savings Bank consumer mortgage customers that do not have an existing checking account with Thomaston Savings Bank
 To receive the $500 bonus: Establish a new noninterest-bearing checking account 90 days prior to or within the 90 days after your mortgage closes
 Enroll in eStatements and have a total of $1,000 in external direct deposits post to your new checking account within 90 days of account opening
 Once all requirements have been met, we will deposit $500 in your new checking account within 10 business days after all criteria was satisfied. Limit one offer per customeriiii. Bonus is considered interest and is subject to reporting on IRS Form 1099-INT (or if applicable, 1042-S). Employees and Corporators of Thomaston Savings Bank are not eligible for this bonus. Offer effective 12/21/2020 and may be withdrawn at any time.
 All bank account bonuses are treated as income/interest and as such you have to pay taxes on them
